entry.title: Master & Dynamic And Leica Camera Partnership
entry.summary:
We are thrilled to announce we’ve partnered once again with Leica Camera AG to introduce two new wireless sound tools to the “Master & Dynamic for 0.95” collection.

More
entry.content:
We are thrilled to announce we’ve partnered once again with Leica Camera AG to introduce two new wireless sound tools to the “Master & Dynamic for 0.95” collection.

Originally launched in 2017, the collection now includes two new additions inspired by the iconic design and unrivalled craftsmanship of the world’s fastest aspherical lens, the Leica Noctilux-M 50mm f/0.95 ASPH, which reveals details that are hidden to the human eye. The collection reimagines our most sophisticated sound tools: MW65 Active Noise-Cancelling Wireless Headphones in matte black metal with black leather and MW07 PLUS True Wireless Earphones in black acetate with a matte black stainless steel charging case.

Each product borrows iconic design elements from the Noctilux lens and the legendary Leica brand including anodized aluminum with matte black finish, gloss detailing, and Leica’s signature red dot marker. A combination of durable cowhide and supple lambskin reminiscent of the leather used on Leica camera bodies and straps comprise the headband and ear pads of the MW65 Wireless Headphones, while Leica’s iconic red marker and signature knurling are apparent throughout. Outfitted with high performance 40mm Beryllium drivers, two modes of Active Noise-Cancellation, and a lightweight anodized aluminum body, the MW65 Wireless Headphones embody the uncompromising commitment to quality both brands are known for.

Likewise, the MW07 PLUS True Wireless Earphones with 40 hours total playtime also feature elevated materials: beautiful handcrafted acetate, a sleek new matte black stainless steel charging case, and custom 10mm Beryllium drivers. The red multifunction button is a nod to Leica’s iconic red marker.

The “Master & Dynamic for 0.95” collection is available here.

entry.title: Master & Dynamic X Automobili Lamborghini
entry.content:
Master & Dynamic is thrilled to partner with Automobili Lamborghini on a collection of high-performance sound tools inspired by the design and materials of the iconic Italian super sports cars. The collaboration products draw from Lamborghini’s legendary DNA, incorporating the hexagon and Y patterns that characterize Lamborghini, and are crafted from the finest materials including Alcantara®, sapphire glass, Italian acetate, anodized aluminum, and stainless steel.

The new collection features MW65 Active Noise-Cancelling Wireless Headphones and MW07 Plus True Wireless Earphones, each in three new colorways. The headphones are available in Silver Metal/Light Grey/Yellow Alcantara®; Black Metal with Black/Yellow Alcantara®; and Black Metal with Black/Grey Alcantara®. Alcantara® is a vegan Italian luxury material widely used in Lamborghini interiors. The earphones are available in three colorways: Polished White with Matte Silver Charging Case, Polished Black with Matte Black Charging Case, and Matte Black with Matte Black Charging Case.

As a young boy obsessed with cars, I remember being mesmerized the first time I saw a Miura. That feeling and excitement is still with me today whenever I see a Lamborghini. To create something that initiates such a visceral response has always been my intention at Master & Dynamic.

Jonathan Levine, Founder and CEO of Master & Dynamic

MW65 Wireless Active Noise-Cancelling Headphones

The MW65 Wireless Active Noise-Cancelling Headphones feature two active noise-cancelling modes to finely tailor sound to your specific surroundings for a clear, balanced listening experience in any environment. Custom 40mm Beryllium drivers deliver Master & Dynamic’s signature rich, warm sound that captures the detail of well-recorded music.

MW07 Plus True Wireless Earphones

The MW07 Plus True Wireless Earphones are a luxe innovation in the True Wireless category, boasting an unparalleled 40 hours of total battery life (with stainless steel charging case) and Bluetooth 5.0 with 30m/100ft connection range. Dual beamforming noise reduction mic arrays, one on each earphone, provide best-in-class talk performance while 10mm custom Beryllium drivers deliver brilliant sound.

entry.title: Master & Dynamic X Paris Saint-Germain F.C.
entry.content:
Master & Dynamic is excited to partner with iconic French football club Paris Saint-Germain on a limited-edition collection of MH40 Wireless Over-Ear Headphones and MW07 PLUS True Wireless Earphones. Designed by Paris Saint-Germain, the limited-edition collection features visionary, galaxy-inspired prints, illustrating the new evolution for the Paris-based club.

Whether we listen to it all day long or not, at home or during a workout, music is part of our everyday lives. More than ever during this time, the comfort and sound quality of headphones or earphones is essential to our acoustic experience. Master & Dynamic has made a place for itself within the very small group of brands that know how to combine the design of the object (thoughtful construction and noble materials) with an advanced sound that reminds the evolution from DVD to Blu Ray! 


The MH40 Wireless Headphones are crafted from anodized aluminum, coated canvas, and lambskin leather. They feature Bluetooth 5.0 with a 30m/100ft connectivity range as well as 40mm Beryllium Drivers for brilliant sound. 

Click here to shop the MH40 Wireless PSG, while stock lasts.

At Master & Dynamic, we are constantly trying to innovate, pushing our products and sound to the next level. Similarly, Paris Saint-Germain’s constant evolution and pioneering spirit inspire us, and we are honored to work with one of the world’s most talented, dedicated teams on two new sound tools.

Jonathan Levine, Founder and CEO of Master & Dynamic


MW07 PLUS True Wireless Earphones are made from handcrafted acetate and housed in a highly reflective stainless steel charging case with an iridescent patina that offers 3 additional charges for 40 hours total playtime. 10mm Beryllium drivers offer a rich, warm sound.

Click here to shop the MW07 Plus PSG, be careful, it's a limited edition!
